 The presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress, Bola Tinubu, and his running mate, Kashim Shettima, have arrived in Port Harcourt, in continuation of their campaign for the presidency. The duo arrived at the Yakubu Gowon Stadium for the party’s presidential rally around 4pm. However, the former Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi, was conspicously absent from the event. Tinubu danced and waved to the cheering crowd before proceeding to the podium. Earlier, the former governors of Ekiti and Edo states, Dr Kayode Fayemi and Adams Oshiomhole respectively, with the Governor of Ebonyi State, Dave Umahi, arrived in Port Harcourt for the presidential rally.